@page "/skiatest"
@using SkiaSharp
@using SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor

<SKCanvasView OnPaintSurface="OnPaintSurface" />

@code {
    private SKSize lastCanvasSize;

    private void OnPaintSurface(SKPaintSurfaceEventArgs e)
    {
        lastCanvasSize = new SKSize(e.Info.Width, e.Info.Height);
    }
}

proposedResponse.body:
Thanks for the suggestion! We've confirmed that `CanvasSize` is indeed missing from the Blazor view components (`SKCanvasView` and `SKGLView`), while it's exposed on all other platform views (WPF, WinForms, WinUI, iOS, macOS, Android, MAUI).

The `Dpi` property was already exposed via PR #1832 using the same pattern (`public double Dpi => dpi;`), so adding `CanvasSize` would be consistent.

**Workaround:** You can access the canvas size from within the `OnPaintSurface` callback via the event args:

```csharp
private SKSize lastCanvasSize;

private void OnPaintSurface(SKPaintSurfaceEventArgs e)
{
    lastCanvasSize = new SKSize(e.Info.Width, e.Info.Height);
    // use lastCanvasSize for layout calculations
}
```

This doesn't help if you need the size outside of the paint callback, but it covers the most common use case.
